</think> <answer>Adding $1$ to the left side and subtracting $\pm x$ from the right side results in $$x = 1 \pm (x-2).$$Now we solve for $x.$<br>Adding $x-2$ to both sides results in $$2x-1 = \pm x+2$$This gives us two equations:<br>\begin{align*} 2x-1 &= x+2 &&\text{ and } && 2x-1 = -(x+2)\\ x &= {3 \over 2} &&\text{ and } && 3x = -1 \end{align*}The second equation does not satisfy, so our answer is $\boxed{3/2}.$</answer>

